    public class MORDefinitionConcept
extends MORConceptBase
implements MORConcept.Define, MORConcept.Disjoint<MORDefinitionConcept>, MORConcept.Equivalent<MORDefinitionConcept>, MORConcept.Classify<MORLinkIndividual>
    A basic implementation for a concept with equivalent, disjoint classes as well as defining restrictions.

    This is an example of how use the Semantic.Descriptors for implement a concept that is synchronised w.r.t. its Disjoint and Equivalent classes as wel as with its Define restrictions and Classifyed individuals.
    Its purpose is only to instanciate the MORAxioms.Concepts for the respective descriptions, as well as call the derived interfaces in the readSemantic() and writeSemantic() methods. All its constructions are based on MORConceptBase in order to automatically manage a grounding ConceptInstance.
    You may want to use this class (see also MORHierarchicalConcept, as well as other classes in the it.emarolab.owloop.aMORDescriptor.utility package) as templates to build a specific MORConcept descriptor that fits your needs and maximises the OWL synchronisation efficiency.

        public java.util.List<Semantic.MappingIntent> readSemantic()
        Description copied from interface: Semantic.Descriptor
